1
00:00:00,574 --> 00:00:02,128
Previously on One Tree Hill.

2
00:00:02,175 --> 00:00:04,898
You passed the band’s test, now you gotta pass mine.

3
00:00:04,957 --> 00:00:07,090
Car salesmen are always such jerks.

4
00:00:07,167 --> 00:00:09,154
- I’m actually a mechanic. 
- I like mechanics.

5
00:00:09,245 --> 00:00:10,664
It’s my first college class.

6
00:00:10,720 --> 00:00:12,927
And you’re taking it with Hargrove? This gut’s tough.

7
00:00:13,014 --> 00:00:15,579
My name’s Andy Hargrove, welcome to my class.

8
00:00:15,651 --> 00:00:19,542
It’s called ‘Dare Night’; one night, two teams, multiple dares.

9
00:00:19,957 --> 00:00:21,150
Oh! My gosh!

10
00:00:21,434 --> 00:00:23,321
- What do we win? 
- A night to remember.

11
00:00:23,378 --> 00:00:24,304
I’m in it to win it.

12
00:00:25,191 --> 00:00:27,735
Three dollars and… eighty cents.

13
00:01:17,450 --> 00:01:19,133
Katherine Anne Porter once said;

14
00:01:19,935 --> 00:01:22,435
There seems to be a kind of order in the universe…

15
00:01:24,663 --> 00:01:27,617
in the movement of the stars and the turning of the Earth

16
00:01:27,745 --> 00:01:29,076
and the changing of the seasons.

17
00:01:30,193 --> 00:01:32,562
But human life is almost pure chaos.

18
00:01:35,845 --> 00:01:37,397
Everyone takes his stance,

19
00:01:38,276 --> 00:01:40,150
asserts his own right and feelings,

20
00:01:40,802 --> 00:01:42,701
mistaking the motives of others,

21
00:01:44,037 --> 00:01:45,072
and his own.

22
00:02:04,901 --> 00:02:07,889
Felix, let’s get going! I don’t wanna be late!

23
00:02:10,279 --> 00:02:11,815
Your skirt’s a little short isn’t it?

24
00:02:13,057 --> 00:02:14,668
I’m just looking out for you.

25
00:02:14,934 --> 00:02:15,846
Can we just go?

26
00:02:16,082 --> 00:02:18,513
Sure, as soon as you discover pants.

27
00:02:18,846 --> 00:02:21,602
You know why? Because first impressions are important Anna.

28
00:02:21,738 --> 00:02:23,679
And yours says all night.

29
00:02:23,925 --> 00:02:25,451
You know what, I’ll ride the bus.

30
00:02:26,225 --> 00:02:27,263
Anna okay!

31
00:02:27,672 --> 00:02:28,953
- Come on!
- No!

32
00:02:29,015 --> 00:02:30,611
- I’m just playing. 
- You’re being mean!

33
00:02:30,694 --> 00:02:32,189
Let me guess.

34
00:02:34,021 --> 00:02:37,663
One of your ‘Friends with Benefits’ hoes didn’t wanna pay her deductible?

35
00:02:37,971 --> 00:02:39,681
Gross, that’s my sister.

36
00:02:40,654 --> 00:02:45,046
Wait! You mean after they had you, your parents rolled the dice and kept breeding?

37
00:02:45,517 --> 00:02:46,382
It’s risky.

38
00:02:46,690 --> 00:02:47,304
Funny!

39
00:02:47,729 --> 00:02:50,454
You know, I was thinking about this whole ‘Friends with Benefits’.

40
00:02:50,930 --> 00:02:52,220
Felix with Brooke.

41
00:02:53,362 --> 00:02:54,641
FWB.

42
00:02:54,903 --> 00:02:59,772
Hmm… IYFD… In Your Dreams.

43
00:03:06,966 --> 00:03:11,988
I saw you in 87; against Williamsburg. You put up, what, thirty-five points?

44
00:03:12,056 --> 00:03:14,206
- Thirty-seven. 
- Man you were unstoppable.

45
00:03:14,985 --> 00:03:16,225
You play college ball?

46
00:03:17,269 --> 00:03:19,285
How long until we have the results.

47
00:03:19,448 --> 00:03:23,510
The doctor will call in a day or two but… his numbers look… good

48
00:03:23,571 --> 00:03:25,180
for a guy who just had a heart attack.

49
00:03:26,019 --> 00:03:28,553
I tell you what I’m gonna put this on warm-down for you, okay?

50
00:03:29,726 --> 00:03:33,429
There, better? How bout that?

51
00:03:33,535 --> 00:03:36,797
- Good, it’s good. 
- Alright, hey you take your time man.

52
00:03:41,896 --> 00:03:46,075
How am I supposed to pass a stress test with some orderly reminding me my best days are behind me?

53
00:03:46,434 --> 00:03:49,388
Come on, he says you’re doing fine.

54
00:03:50,805 --> 00:03:51,611
Thanks.

55
00:03:52,477 --> 00:03:56,264
You must be happy; in forty-eight hours… you won’t have to wait on me anymore.

56
00:03:59,753 --> 00:04:02,485
Well I’m not going to put my mind on waiting for a phone call.

57
00:04:03,541 --> 00:04:05,957
Word in the paper, there’s gonna be a meteor shower this weekend.

58
00:04:06,680 --> 00:04:08,620
Thought maybe I’d got out and watch it from the beach house.

59
00:04:09,296 --> 00:04:10,310
Good for you, Dan.

60
00:04:12,471 --> 00:04:13,971
Maybe we could watch it together.

61
00:04:17,530 --> 00:04:19,711
You’ve been with me every step of this recovery Deb.

62
00:04:21,452 --> 00:04:24,888
We could go out there and… I could make you dinner. Just to say thanks.

63
00:04:25,892 --> 00:04:26,705
That’s all.

64
00:04:31,268 --> 00:04:32,461
Sorry, we’re closed.

65
00:04:32,747 --> 00:04:36,997
Yeah, I know... I was just wondering if I could post this flyer on your board.

66
00:04:37,208 --> 00:04:39,722
I’m… auditioning bands for a local talent night.

67
00:04:39,905 --> 00:04:41,114
‘All-Ages’ night.

68
00:04:41,749 --> 00:04:44,084
Tell you what, you can post it if you take your shirt off.

69
00:04:45,411 --> 00:04:49,614
- Excuse me?! 
- Emo’s crap. Gives punk a bad name.

70
00:04:49,999 --> 00:04:51,625
- You think? 
- I do.

71
00:04:52,011 --> 00:04:56,107
Huh, well I guess those who can’t do, sell records!

72
00:04:56,209 --> 00:04:57,971
You insult all your customers this way?

73
00:04:58,043 --> 00:05:01,141
Well since we’re not really open, you’re not really a customer.

74
00:05:02,343 --> 00:05:03,848
Whatever, I’m going to school.

75
00:05:03,909 --> 00:05:05,980
Don’t forget your Get-Up-Kids lunchbox.

76
00:05:07,365 --> 00:05:10,556
You know, its real punk to be up at seven a.m. doing inventory.

77
00:05:11,632 --> 00:05:13,050
I never went to sleep.

78
00:05:19,604 --> 00:05:20,616
Hello?

79
00:05:21,007 --> 00:05:22,272
Jules, its Keith.

80
00:05:23,903 --> 00:05:26,188
Keith, you know, the guy who took you on that drive.

81
00:05:27,135 --> 00:05:28,118
Gotcha.

82
00:05:29,490 --> 00:05:35,088
Well the reason I’m calling is the… follow-up customer satisfaction survey.

83
00:05:35,163 --> 00:05:40,357
On a scale of one to ten; how happy were you with the service at ‘Dan Scott Motors’?

84
00:05:41,227 --> 00:05:45,769
Well the guy who helped me was nice and… kinda cute.

85
00:05:45,876 --> 00:05:48,364
But he waited a whole week to call me and when he did,

86
00:05:48,431 --> 00:05:51,129
he came up with some lame excuse about a survey.

87
00:05:51,424 --> 00:05:52,483
I’d give him a seven.

88
00:05:52,824 --> 00:05:55,334
Well you think we could, uh, bump that up to an eight or a nine?

89
00:05:55,560 --> 00:05:57,402
Maybe over dinner tomorrow night.

90
00:05:57,888 --> 00:06:00,936
Maybe if he comes to my place and cooks for me.

91
00:06:01,397 --> 00:06:02,158
Okay.

92
00:06:11,883 --> 00:06:12,652
Hey Coach.

93
00:06:12,911 --> 00:06:13,853
Scott!

94
00:06:15,006 --> 00:06:16,081
How you feeling?

95
00:06:16,203 --> 00:06:19,937
Oh, like a school girl in springtime. What can I do for ya?

96
00:06:20,019 --> 00:06:24,248
Well… I just wanted to talk to you about your surgery.

97
00:06:25,005 --> 00:06:28,478
- Keith had told me that...
- Who gives a damn what Keith says?

98
00:06:28,913 --> 00:06:30,321
It’s not his life.

99
00:06:31,519 --> 00:06:35,339
Okay… I just don’t know why you’re not going through with the surgery.

100
00:06:38,221 --> 00:06:40,668
Lucas, do you know how my wife died?

101
00:06:41,698 --> 00:06:46,788
In surgery. Like twenty thousand other people a year and I don’t plan to be one of them!

102
00:06:46,874 --> 00:06:49,102
- Look, Coach. 
- No, you look!

103
00:06:49,578 --> 00:06:52,282
We are not in season, there’s no practice.

104
00:06:52,636 --> 00:06:57,530
Now I want you to turn around and get out of my office and mind your own damn business!

105
00:07:08,442 --> 00:07:10,408
This club night, is gonna rule!

106
00:07:10,495 --> 00:07:12,688
Not according to the jerk at the record store.

107
00:07:13,324 --> 00:07:14,720
What are these auditions?

108
00:07:15,083 --> 00:07:19,957
Oh… I think Peyton’s having like an ‘All-Ages’ night at the… at Karen’s Club.

109
00:07:20,035 --> 00:07:21,423
She’s kinda looking for bands or something.

110
00:07:21,525 --> 00:07:24,325
- When do you go on? 
- Not! Stop it.

111
00:07:24,397 --> 00:07:25,058
Hales!

112
00:07:25,765 --> 00:07:29,196
It’s one thing to play at home for you, it’s another to get up in front of a crowd to do it

113
00:07:29,281 --> 00:07:30,322
and there’s no way.

114
00:07:31,013 --> 00:07:34,269
Nathan, letter came for you through my office.

115
00:07:34,935 --> 00:07:35,682
What is it?

116
00:07:35,989 --> 00:07:39,817
How the hell should I know?! Do I look like the damn postmaster general?!

117
00:07:42,036 --> 00:07:45,702
A meteor shower occurs when the Earth passes through the cloud of dust

118
00:07:45,769 --> 00:07:48,669
left behind by a comet, in its orbit of the sun.

119
00:07:53,737 --> 00:07:54,458
Here you go.

120
00:07:56,267 --> 00:07:57,895
Lucas, you’re wanted in the office.

121
00:07:58,837 --> 00:07:59,711
Take your books.

122
00:08:05,171 --> 00:08:05,893
Hey.

123
00:08:06,133 --> 00:08:06,911
Anna?

124
00:08:07,832 --> 00:08:09,022
What are you doing here?

125
00:08:09,394 --> 00:08:12,040
I’m sorry I didn’t call you after ‘Dare Night’.

126
00:08:13,122 --> 00:08:14,813
Give me a chance to explain.

127
00:08:15,231 --> 00:08:16,306
I mean, you owe me that.

128
00:08:17,597 --> 00:08:18,559
I owe you?

129
00:08:19,144 --> 00:08:20,844
I got you out of Science didn’t I?

130
00:08:22,665 --> 00:08:24,469
Where did you get this Hall Pass anyway?

131
00:08:24,872 --> 00:08:26,839
I swiped it, when I met the principle.

132
00:08:27,162 --> 00:08:31,918
Look, I’m sorry I blew you off. My brother’s kind of… overprotective.

133
00:08:31,982 --> 00:08:34,064
Because we haven’t gone to the same school in a few years and...

134
00:08:34,146 --> 00:08:35,774
Wait, Felix is your brother?

135
00:08:35,897 --> 00:08:36,543
Um…

136
00:08:38,677 --> 00:08:39,492
yeah.

137
00:08:40,655 --> 00:08:43,039
I figured you’d connect the dots sooner or later.

138
00:08:44,628 --> 00:08:50,516
Anyway... I told Felix that I hadn’t met any guys and…

139
00:08:50,767 --> 00:08:54,140
I don’t know, I just didn’t wanna have to deal with him so I didn’t call you.

140
00:08:54,212 --> 00:08:57,946
I’m sorry. I figured when Felix saw those pictures of us in the photo booth,

141
00:08:58,042 --> 00:08:59,508
he’d let you know who I was.

142
00:08:59,911 --> 00:09:02,989
You know, I still can’t figure if he’s screwing with me or what.

143
00:09:04,142 --> 00:09:05,827
I never gave him the pictures.

144
00:09:07,751 --> 00:09:08,621
Why?

145
00:09:11,326 --> 00:09:13,276
Because it wasn’t just about ‘Dare Night’ for me.

146
00:09:15,385 --> 00:09:16,159
Me neither.

147
00:09:25,079 --> 00:09:27,945
That’s a decaf latte with one shot of Irish cream.

148
00:09:28,648 --> 00:09:29,328
Thanks.

149
00:09:29,533 --> 00:09:32,875
Ah, you’ve been pouring me free coffee in the café a week, I figured I’d return the favour.

150
00:09:33,266 --> 00:09:36,805
Well unlike you I need an ‘A’, consider that coffee my apple.

151
00:09:37,372 --> 00:09:40,254
Um, so look. I was wondering if you were available tomorrow night,

152
00:09:40,322 --> 00:09:42,380
to… to watch the meteor shower.

153
00:09:44,321 --> 00:09:45,340
Just the two of us?

154
00:09:46,997 --> 00:09:50,107
Well I could… schedule a… class… felid trip if it makes you feel safer.

155
00:09:50,163 --> 00:09:51,571
Oh no no no. That’s not it.

156
00:09:52,829 --> 00:09:56,113
It’s just that… going back to school was a big step for me.

157
00:09:57,838 --> 00:10:03,532
And you’re afraid that you’ll screw it up. Like… I don’t know, dating your professor. Yes.

158
00:10:07,383 --> 00:10:07,997
Karen…

159
00:10:11,371 --> 00:10:14,633
I wouldn’t ask you to hang out with me if I thought it was gonna compromise your studies,

160
00:10:15,129 --> 00:10:15,922
or my job.

161
00:10:18,708 --> 00:10:22,487
You know, unless… unless you, you know, simply don’t wanna hang out with me

162
00:10:22,543 --> 00:10:25,688
- because that’s okay too. 
- Oh no, no no, I do. That’s... not it.

163
00:10:26,947 --> 00:10:27,787
Good.

164
00:10:30,249 --> 00:10:32,615
So... so what do you say? Tomorrow night?

165
00:10:34,224 --> 00:10:34,981
Okay.

166
00:10:35,802 --> 00:10:36,852
Good.

167
00:10:38,005 --> 00:10:39,288
Well I’ll leave you too it.

168
00:10:40,884 --> 00:10:45,548
Oh and, hey, I know it’s kinda short notice so… bring Lucas along if you can’t find a sitter.

169
00:10:45,600 --> 00:10:46,645
Love to meet the little guy.

170
00:10:48,590 --> 00:10:50,562
Oh I don’t think that’s gonna be a problem.

171
00:10:52,021 --> 00:10:52,727
Okay.

172
00:10:57,844 --> 00:11:02,954
Stars. To the human eye they appear very close together but as you know, in reality...

173
00:11:03,036 --> 00:11:06,240
‘High Flyers’ is like this Allstar basketball boot camp.

174
00:11:06,374 --> 00:11:09,446
And this guy Milt West, he scouts the best players in the country

175
00:11:09,502 --> 00:11:11,760
and invites them down to Florida so they can work on their skills.

176
00:11:11,827 --> 00:11:13,469
And invited you. Wow.

177
00:11:13,870 --> 00:11:18,595
Nathan, I’m really happy for you. You deserve this you’ve… you’ve worked really hard.

178
00:11:25,431 --> 00:11:27,485
Okay, could it get any worse?

179
00:11:27,996 --> 00:11:31,852
My love life is non-existent, my parents are having a yard sale to sell everything that we own

180
00:11:31,904 --> 00:11:33,977
and I had to beg them to keep my car.

181
00:11:34,110 --> 00:11:34,940
Okay.

182
00:11:35,247 --> 00:11:38,682
You might not be rich but you are still Brooke Davis;

183
00:11:38,759 --> 00:11:41,673
the most popular, least studious girl in school.

184
00:11:41,821 --> 00:11:46,036
Maybe so, but being poor and horny is no way to go through life.

185
00:11:46,117 --> 00:11:47,622
How am I supposed to have fun?

186
00:11:48,217 --> 00:11:52,728
Boys won’t care about the poor part, just as long as you tell them about the horny part.

187
00:11:52,897 --> 00:11:55,134
To top it all off, if my parents go broke,

188
00:11:55,211 --> 00:11:58,622
I might actually have to study to get into college.

189
00:11:58,693 --> 00:12:00,940
My God the horror!

190
00:12:01,120 --> 00:12:02,186
I know!

191
00:12:02,528 --> 00:12:04,427
How the mighty have fallen.

192
00:12:19,272 --> 00:12:21,407
I think I need a little recess.

193
00:12:21,996 --> 00:12:25,815
What do you get when two, flaming, stellar bodies collide?

194
00:12:27,372 --> 00:12:30,624
Okay, here’s the thing; we are not dating, we are not going out, we are nothing.

195
00:12:30,685 --> 00:12:32,779
I am not your wife, your shrink, your mommy.

196
00:12:32,836 --> 00:12:36,322
There’s no romance, no crappy poetry, no PDA and no spooning.

197
00:12:36,419 --> 00:12:39,547
This is purely physical. If we have sex, it’s gonna be safe sex;

198
00:12:39,616 --> 00:12:42,728
we’re ‘Friends with Benefits’ and in fact, we don’t even need to talk.

199
00:12:42,840 --> 00:12:44,208
- I can live with that. 
- Great!

200
00:12:51,053 --> 00:12:55,544
So, there’s this new girl, named Anna, in my algebra class.

201
00:12:56,721 --> 00:12:58,375
She be the ‘Dare Night’ mystery girl?

202
00:12:58,565 --> 00:13:02,267
Yeah. Also happens to be Felix’s sister.

203
00:13:02,850 --> 00:13:05,631
Nice! D’you know bout that?

204
00:13:05,759 --> 00:13:07,234
Just found out this morning.

205
00:13:07,531 --> 00:13:11,140
Well don’t hold it against her man, she can’t help it if her brother’s an ass.

206
00:13:13,403 --> 00:13:14,581
So ‘High Flyers’?

207
00:13:15,110 --> 00:13:19,113
I mean, what I wouldn’t give, three months in Florida, playing basketball at that camp.

208
00:13:20,403 --> 00:13:21,595
Is it three months?

209
00:13:22,087 --> 00:13:23,310
Yeah, I think so. Why?

210
00:13:24,618 --> 00:13:25,826
That’s all summer.

211
00:13:25,958 --> 00:13:30,039
I mean, we can’t live for three months off Haley’s café paycheque.

212
00:13:30,285 --> 00:13:32,877
And even if we could, I mean I don’t wanna be apart from her that long.

213
00:13:33,388 --> 00:13:34,852
You guys will figure it out.

214
00:13:36,982 --> 00:13:40,562
Nathan, this is a once in a lifetime opportunity…

215
00:13:41,576 --> 00:13:42,620
you know that.

216
00:13:56,387 --> 00:13:57,853
What are you doing here?

217
00:13:58,466 --> 00:13:59,995
I just wanted to say hello.

218
00:14:01,565 --> 00:14:02,953
You’ve said it.

219
00:14:07,044 --> 00:14:08,651
Nathan got into ‘High Flyers’.

220
00:14:10,899 --> 00:14:13,040
And he couldn’t have done it without you so I…

221
00:14:15,082 --> 00:14:16,630
I just thought you’d care to know.

222
00:14:18,457 --> 00:14:19,307
Son!

223
00:14:20,623 --> 00:14:23,725
The mistake you’re making is - you think I care;

224
00:14:24,360 --> 00:14:28,661
about you, about the team, about anything.

225
00:14:30,801 --> 00:14:34,126
I lost the only thing I cared about a long time ago.

226
00:14:39,451 --> 00:14:41,974
You know, I have this picture in my room of the team…

227
00:14:43,455 --> 00:14:45,205
from your five-hundredth win.

228
00:14:47,213 --> 00:14:50,377
And the man in that photo still looks like a guy to me that still cares about something.

229
00:14:52,036 --> 00:14:53,346
We need you, Coach.

230
00:14:53,991 --> 00:14:56,804
Not just to win games, we need you in our lives!

231
00:15:05,359 --> 00:15:06,572
Have the surgery.

232
00:15:18,634 --> 00:15:20,945
Oh, I figured this summer out. I thought I would call Karen -

233
00:15:21,007 --> 00:15:22,861
see if I could stay with her and Lucas for a little while,

234
00:15:22,942 --> 00:15:25,721
till you get back or like, rent a room from her. We’ll save a ton.

235
00:15:25,779 --> 00:15:27,033
- Think she’ll go for that? 
- Oh please!

236
00:15:27,080 --> 00:15:29,244
Before you came along, I practically lived there anyway.

237
00:15:29,470 --> 00:15:33,035
- Then I’ll pick up some extra shifts at the café...
- Haley, you work enough already.

238
00:15:33,106 --> 00:15:35,528
Hey, you’re gonna go to this camp if I have to sell a kidney.

239
00:15:35,983 --> 00:15:37,627
It’s only three months, I just…

240
00:15:38,139 --> 00:15:40,254
wish I could go to Florida with you.

241
00:15:42,844 --> 00:15:44,089
Isn’t this Brooke’s house?

242
00:15:44,749 --> 00:15:46,553
