Girls like you, giving them the benefit of the doubt.

489
00:36:24,808 --> 00:36:29,791
Oh! You just took ten years off my life.

490
00:36:29,889 --> 00:36:31,302
It’s one o’clock in the morning.

491
00:36:32,197 --> 00:36:34,682
I have been worried sick. Where have you been?

492
00:36:35,076 --> 00:36:39,925
- I’m sorry, it just...
- No, after midnight, you call.

493
00:36:43,960 --> 00:36:45,909
I really hope I don’t sound like that!

494
00:36:47,544 --> 00:36:48,957
How long have you been home?

495
00:36:49,101 --> 00:36:50,561
Oh, bout five minutes.

496
00:36:51,042 --> 00:36:52,572
Well then we’re both grounded.

497
00:36:53,238 --> 00:36:54,881
Clearly a rookie mom.

498
00:36:54,974 --> 00:36:57,467
Next time, try sneaking in the window.

499
00:36:59,623 --> 00:37:00,846
So, did you have a good time?

500
00:37:03,010 --> 00:37:04,377
Yeah, I did.

501
00:37:07,128 --> 00:37:07,918
Good.

502
00:37:15,426 --> 00:37:17,262
Hey. I’m making pancakes.

503
00:37:17,666 --> 00:37:20,170
Oh, I’m sorry, Dan, I’m going home.

504
00:37:21,512 --> 00:37:23,678
What’s the hurry? We’ll go back in a few hours.

505
00:37:24,057 --> 00:37:25,454
Oh, no we won’t.

506
00:37:25,875 --> 00:37:30,180
Coming out here was a mistake. I can’t… keep pretending that things are normal.

507
00:37:31,056 --> 00:37:33,708
You’re better now, so…

508
00:37:34,805 --> 00:37:36,684
I’ll send your things over.

509
00:37:40,176 --> 00:37:41,163
It’s the doctor.

510
00:37:43,493 --> 00:37:45,910
- Dan Scott! 
- Hi Dan, this is Doctor Connelly.

511
00:37:45,983 --> 00:37:49,223
I just received your test results back from the lab. You’re doing really well

512
00:37:49,320 --> 00:37:52,358
and we can now start talking about a more strenuous exercise programme.

513
00:37:53,334 --> 00:37:54,112
I see.

514
00:37:54,185 --> 00:37:55,799
So call my office and set up an appointment.

515
00:37:55,869 --> 00:37:58,127
Thank you doctor, I will. Thank you.

516
00:38:04,053 --> 00:38:05,402
It’s not good.

517
00:38:05,956 --> 00:38:07,897
I’m gonna have to stay with you for a while.

518
00:38:10,566 --> 00:38:11,362
Come in!

519
00:38:11,819 --> 00:38:12,946
- Hey man. 
- Hey.

520
00:38:13,274 --> 00:38:16,882
Wanna help me with this table? I’m rearranging so Haley has more room to practice.

521
00:38:17,257 --> 00:38:19,899
- Yeah man, where do you want it? 
- Right there.

522
00:38:21,604 --> 00:38:25,379
So Haley told me you didn’t get into ‘High Flyers’ after all. Tough break.

523
00:38:25,465 --> 00:38:26,812
Yeah, it’s too bad.

524
00:38:28,045 --> 00:38:29,253
You did get in.

525
00:38:31,343 --> 00:38:34,994
Nathan, man you’ve been working for your whole life for this.

526
00:38:36,217 --> 00:38:37,549
You can’t say no.

527
00:38:38,510 --> 00:38:40,626
You know what it’s like to hit a game winning shot.

528
00:38:41,322 --> 00:38:45,393
The whole crowd loves you… everybody treats you like you’re a star.

529
00:38:47,093 --> 00:38:50,965
I get to feel that every time I play. I mean, you know, you’ve felt it.

530
00:38:51,711 --> 00:38:55,807
Now, it’s Haley’s turn. I mean she’s an incredible musician, Luke,

531
00:38:55,925 --> 00:38:57,824
and she’s ready to give it a shot.

532
00:38:58,270 --> 00:39:00,611
So if I got to camp now, for three months,

533
00:39:01,210 --> 00:39:02,890
who knows where her head’s gonna be.

534
00:39:04,322 --> 00:39:07,728
I just really want her to feel, like, the thrill of the crowd.

535
00:39:08,839 --> 00:39:09,959
She deserves it.

536
00:39:11,076 --> 00:39:12,433
Well what about your future?

537
00:39:13,985 --> 00:39:15,511
I already know my future.

538
00:39:16,678 --> 00:39:17,938
It’s with Haley.

539
00:39:36,975 --> 00:39:38,465
Welcome to ‘TRIC’.

540
00:39:44,809 --> 00:39:47,261
- Nice space. 
- Oh, Rick.

541
00:39:47,339 --> 00:39:52,356
Here you’re looking for bands. Suppose we’re working together after all.

542
00:39:54,963 --> 00:39:58,071
I guess… we’ll be partying together too.

543
00:40:09,392 --> 00:40:10,374
Mouth!

544
00:40:11,291 --> 00:40:14,189
I… I knew this meant a lot to you.

545
00:40:14,555 --> 00:40:18,214
So, I got the address off the woman’s cheque and…

546
00:40:18,440 --> 00:40:19,674
I bought it back.

547
00:40:30,333 --> 00:40:31,512
Thank you.

548
00:40:34,031 --> 00:40:34,743
Yeah!

549
00:40:34,810 --> 00:40:37,097
Hey Dan, Milt West from ‘High Flyers’.

550
00:40:37,742 --> 00:40:39,832
Uh… your son, turned me down.

551
00:40:40,350 --> 00:40:43,171
So, what? You saying he’s not going to the camp?

552
00:40:43,421 --> 00:40:44,911
You told me you could make this happen.

553
00:40:45,019 --> 00:40:48,209
Says he doesn’t wanna be away from his wife. Sorry.

554
00:41:09,961 --> 00:41:13,473
So I… I want you to know that I met somebody.

555
00:41:14,717 --> 00:41:16,975
Well that’s cool. So did I.

556
00:41:18,117 --> 00:41:20,246
Well, mine’s younger than me.

557
00:41:20,909 --> 00:41:22,530
I mean a lot younger.

558
00:41:24,905 --> 00:41:25,966
Okay.

559
00:41:26,596 --> 00:41:29,074
Well if he’s younger than me, I’m not calling him dad.

560
00:41:32,391 --> 00:41:34,517
Oh, this came for you.

